      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Confusion on Ticket, Invoice & Payment -> why we need 3 instead of 1",
      "fontSize": 54.280933418573134,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Confusion on Ticket, Invoice & Payment -> why we need 3 instead of 1",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "0x4LOhovc9BsjaaqgmHCp",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4998.069352647493,
      "y": 7844.412559280565,
      "width": 2000.591796875,
      "height": 189.46794279564355,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#d0bfff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bEL",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1737283789,
      "version": 278,
      "versionNonce": 89560365,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770043215409,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Confusion 2 ->why we need status in all ticket, \n        Invoice and payment",
      "fontSize": 75.78717711825742,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Confusion 2 ->why we need status in all ticket, \n        Invoice and payment",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "6BoK8P_g8hS4SLStPCQTn",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4981.79202305911,
      "y": 8154.1284589204115,
      "width": 1148.3992919921875,
      "height": 1530,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#d0bfff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bEM",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1198667565,
      "version": 246,
      "versionNonce": 293955469,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770043215409,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "First: One Golden Rule 🧠\n\nStatus belongs to the thing whose lifecycle we care about.\n\nIf something:\n\nlives for some time\nchanges behavior over time\nparticipates in business rules\n\n👉 it needs a status\n\nNow apply this rule\n1️⃣ Ticket — WHY it needs status 🎫\n\nWhat Ticket represents\n“Vehicle is/was parked.”\n\nTicket lifecycle\nCREATED → ACTIVE → CLOSED / LOST\n\nWhy status is needed\n\nIs the vehicle still inside?\nCan exit gate accept this ticket?\nCan invoice be generated?\nIs this ticket already used?\n\n\nif ticket.status != \"ACTIVE\":\n    raise Exception(\"Invalid ticket\")\n\n\n✅ Ticket is long-lived → needs status",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "First: One Golden Rule 🧠\n\nStatus belongs to the thing whose lifecycle we care about.\n\nIf something:\n\nlives for some time\nchanges behavior over time\nparticipates in business rules\n\n👉 it needs a status\n\nNow apply this rule\n1️⃣ Ticket — WHY it needs status 🎫\n\nWhat Ticket represents\n“Vehicle is/was parked.”\n\nTicket lifecycle\nCREATED → ACTIVE → CLOSED / LOST\n\nWhy status is needed\n\nIs the vehicle still inside?\nCan exit gate accept this ticket?\nCan invoice be generated?\nIs this ticket already used?\n\n\nif ticket.status != \"ACTIVE\":\n    raise Exception(\"Invalid ticket\")\n\n\n✅ Ticket is long-lived → needs status",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "8mde0ktgFqIOPS7h7dlcn",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 6171.690873821561,
      "y": 8705.852227565822,
      "width": 1243.7991943359375,
      "height": 900,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#d0bfff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bEN",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 333236621,
      "version": 175,
      "versionNonce": 686484973,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770043215409,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "2️⃣ Invoice — WHY it needs status 🧾\n\nWhat Invoice represents\n“This is the bill for parking.”\n\nInvoice lifecycle\nCREATED → PAID → CANCELLED / EXPIRED\n\nWhy status is needed\n\nHas payment already been done?\nShould we allow retry?\nCan we refund?\nIs the bill still valid?\n\nif invoice.status == \"PAID\":\n    block_exit()\n\n\n✅ Invoice represents a financial obligation → MUST have status",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "2️⃣ Invoice — WHY it needs status 🧾\n\nWhat Invoice represents\n“This is the bill for parking.”\n\nInvoice lifecycle\nCREATED → PAID → CANCELLED / EXPIRED\n\nWhy status is needed\n\nHas payment already been done?\nShould we allow retry?\nCan we refund?\nIs the bill still valid?\n\nif invoice.status == \"PAID\":\n    block_exit()\n\n\n✅ Invoice represents a financial obligation → MUST have status",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "FB5AnlxsGBP1thd4Dr3KM",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 4967.460218668979,
      "y": 9934.664130977348,
      "width": 1781.999267578125,
      "height": 3195,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "#d0bfff",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bEO",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1845891053,
      "version": 260,
      "versionNonce": 445687885,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770043215409,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Payment ->\n\nShort answer (clear & honest)\n\nWe need status in Payment only when payment is NOT an instant, one-shot operation.\nIf payment can fail, retry, stay pending, or be refunded, then Payment MUST have a status.\n\n\nThink of Payment as a STATE MACHINE 💳\n\nPayment is not money — it is a process.\n\nWhenever a process:\n\nspans time\ntalks to an external system\ncan be retried\ncan end in different outcomes\n👉 it needs a status.\n\nWhen Payment DOES NOT need status ❌\nSimple synchronous flow\npay() → success / failure → done\n\nExample:\n\nCash payment\nSimple in-memory demo\nOne API call, one response\n\nsuccess = gateway.pay(amount)\nif success:\n    invoice.status = \"PAID\"\n\nHere:\n\nPayment object is just a record\nInvoice status is enough\n\n\nWhen Payment MUST have status ✅ (Real systems)\n\nCase 1️⃣ Asynchronous gateways\n\nUPI / Card / Wallet\nINITIATED → PENDING → SUCCESS / FAILED\n\n\nWhy?\n\nGateway response may take time\nUser may close app\nCallback/webhook arrives later\n\nCase 2️⃣ Retry support\n\nFAILED → RETRY → SUCCESS\nYou need to know:\n\nHow many attempts?\nWhich one succeeded?\nWhich failed?\n\n\nCase 3️⃣ Partial payments\n\nPARTIAL → PENDING → COMPLETE\nExample:\n\nWallet + Card\nCoupon + Online payment",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Payment ->\n\nShort answer (clear & honest)\n\nWe need status in Payment only when payment is NOT an instant, one-shot operation.\nIf payment can fail, retry, stay pending, or be refunded, then Payment MUST have a status.\n\n\nThink of Payment as a STATE MACHINE 💳\n\nPayment is not money — it is a process.\n\nWhenever a process:\n\nspans time\ntalks to an external system\ncan be retried\ncan end in different outcomes\n👉 it needs a status.\n\nWhen Payment DOES NOT need status ❌\nSimple synchronous flow\npay() → success / failure → done\n\nExample:\n\nCash payment\nSimple in-memory demo\nOne API call, one response\n\nsuccess = gateway.pay(amount)\nif success:\n    invoice.status = \"PAID\"\n\nHere:\n\nPayment object is just a record\nInvoice status is enough\n\n\nWhen Payment MUST have status ✅ (Real systems)\n\nCase 1️⃣ Asynchronous gateways\n\nUPI / Card / Wallet\nINITIATED → PENDING → SUCCESS / FAILED\n\n\nWhy?\n\nGateway response may take time\nUser may close app\nCallback/webhook arrives later\n\nCase 2️⃣ Retry support\n\nFAILED → RETRY → SUCCESS\nYou need to know:\n\nHow many attempts?\nWhich one succeeded?\nWhich failed?\n\n\nCase 3️⃣ Partial payments\n\nPARTIAL → PENDING → COMPLETE\nExample:\n\nWallet + Card\nCoupon + Online payment",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
