      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1770732819208,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "🧠 First: What is Payment responsible for?\n✅ Payment SHOULD\n\nTake an Invoice\nTrack payment status\nSupport multiple payment modes\nBe retryable / fail-safe\n\n❌ Payment SHOULD NOT\n\nCalculate amount\nKnow parking logic\nModify invoice\n\nCore Concepts We’ll Add\n\nPaymentStatus (state)\nPaymentMethod (strategy)\nPayment (entity)\nPaymentService (orchestrator – optional but clean)",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "🧠 First: What is Payment responsible for?\n✅ Payment SHOULD\n\nTake an Invoice\nTrack payment status\nSupport multiple payment modes\nBe retryable / fail-safe\n\n❌ Payment SHOULD NOT\n\nCalculate amount\nKnow parking logic\nModify invoice\n\nCore Concepts We’ll Add\n\nPaymentStatus (state)\nPaymentMethod (strategy)\nPayment (entity)\nPaymentService (orchestrator – optional but clean)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "PDfofB1u3VGW0vQdgoeEh",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1608.4106895385714,
      "y": 23613.08556248435,
      "width": 455.39971923828125,
      "height": 180,
